      "message": "IMHO this is fine. This is very difficult to explain, and you know, I\u0027m not a native English speaker. But my intuition is that if the message is simple enough like \"X is %d, want %d\" or \"X got %d, want \"%d\" it is fine to use a comma at least, and there are many other cases a comma is fine (or preferred). I\u0027m happy to discuss this offline.\n\nBTW, as an objective metric, there are many more \"got, want\" than \"got; want\" in Google internal:\n\nhttps://cs.corp.google.com/search/?q\u003dt.(Error%7CFatal).*got.*,%5C+want%5C++file:_test.go\u0026type\u003dcs\nhttps://cs.corp.google.com/search/?q\u003dt.(Error%7CFatal).*got.*;%5C+want%5C++file:_test.go\u0026type\u003dcs",
